Overview of construction designing in Estonia. Sources of historical construction design projects. Tradition of drawing up project documents. Analyses of project documents and the skill of reading the plans. Rural architecture, analyses of the type of construction, drawing up plans (plan, views, cuts, knots, model).Objectives/eesmärkid:  Developing the skills of project analysis and the skills of graphic presentation of design documentation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course students:
- have an overview of the availability of historical architectural information;
- can apply archive information to preparing design documentation;
- know the history of design and planning in Estonia;
- can read the design documentation of different types of buildings from different periods;
- knows contemporary design standards;
- knows design documentation;
- can prepare the specification of rooms of a building;
- can lay out the specification of rooms in a draft;
- can prepare the specification of rooms for a building in a draft.
